            <details>
                <summary class="sum1">
                    History of Virtualization
                </summary>
    
                <ul>
                    <li>
                    IBM was developing hypervisors in the 1960s.
                    <br />
                    SIMMON and CP-40
                    </li>
                    <li>
                    The formal requirements for virtualization were laid out in
                    a 1974 paper (Popek and Goldberg).
                    </li>
                    <li>
                    In the 1990s, VMware was created, offering type 1 and type 2
                    hypervisors.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                    Other products: Xen, KVM, VirtualBox, Hyper-V, Parallels.
                    </li>
                </ul>

            </details>

